result.execSummary:
The defendant Austin Lee Salo was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Austin Lee Salo is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Austin Lee Salo was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Repeater, Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Austin Lee Salo was found guilty of Criminal Damage to Property [Modifiers: Repeater, Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).
  • Austin Lee Salo was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

3:30 PM Defendant Austin Lee Salo in court, in custody.  Attorney Joseph Foster Rosenthal in court for Austin Lee Salo.  Attorney Allison Cogbill in court for State of Wisconsin. Parties notes that an agreement has been reached. State recites agreement. Defendant will plead to counts 1, 2 and 3 with all modifiers in the complaint. Sentence will be 57 days jail with 57 days credit, time served, sentence will run consecutive to any other sentence. Payment of court costs and surcharges.
Defendant pleads no contest to counts 1, 2, and 3. Attorney Rosenthal stipulates to a factual basis. Court finds that the defendant's pleas have been freely, voluntarily, and intelligently made. Court accepts the defendant's pleas and finds the defendant guilty. Count 4 is dismissed.
Court orders 57 days jail with 57 days credit, time served, sentence will run on each count concurrent to each other but consecutive to any other sentence. Payment of court costs and surcharges.
